- Complete support to Combatant Commands (CCMDs) by demonstrating and assessing intermediate force
capabilities in vessel interdiction and counter-migration exercises.
- Complete modeling and simulation of intermediate force capabilities in warfighter training/gaming models
and performance effects data collection/population to demonstrate/analyze non-lethal effects and support
optimization of training.
- Complete evaluation of intermediate force capabilities by Service warfighting laboratories and Joint Staff, J7,
Joint and Coalition Warfighting for direct user feedback of various non-lethal (NL) technologies and munitions to
include policy and strategy and strategic communication.
- Complete engagement with NATO on cooperative security efforts, to include providing input for Systems
Analysis and Studies (SAS) Panels and NATO assessment of intermediate force capabilities in appropriate allied
scenarios and exercises.
- Complete interaction with Combatant Commander Staffs to evaluate emerging intermediate force capabilities
and their utility in theater operations and Defense of the Homeland missions.
- Complete program management support for Joint and Allied Exercise, Experimentation, Demonstration, and
Assessment efforts.
