Title: Joint Knowledge Development & Distribution Capability (JKDDC)                                                                       0.808       0.808           -
Description: Joint Knowledge Online (JKO) is the Department of War's premier online training platform, designed to enhance the
readiness and preparation of military and civilian personnel. JKO provides advanced technology initiatives, including the Learning
Management System (LMS) application, Course Builder, Warrior Readiness Site (WRS), and Virtual Classroom (VCLASS) training
applications. These capabilities enable scalable and accessible training for hundreds of thousands of personnel deploying to
Combatant Command (CCMD) theaters of operation and serving in Combined/Joint Task Force (C/JTF) billets.
The JKO Learning Management System (LMS) supports the development, hosting, delivery, tracking, and reporting of training
courses, ensuring efficient management of students’ progress, completions, and survey results. Course Builder facilitates the
creation of mission-specific Joint training courses, while the Warrior Readiness Site (WRS) provides centralized resources for pre-
deployment preparation. The Virtual Classroom (VCLASS) enables real-time, interactive training sessions, fostering collaborative
learning environments for individuals and staffs.
By leveraging these advanced capabilities, JKO plays a critical role in preparing the Globally Integrated Joint Force and
Combatant Command (CCMD) personnel. The platform ensures that both individuals and staffs are better trained to meet the
demands of Joint and Combined operations, contributing to the overall effectiveness of the joint training enterprise and supporting
mission success.

FY 2026 Plans:
The Joint Knowledge Online (JKO) program will continue to integrate and expand the Virtual Classroom (VCLASS) open-source
capability (Sakai) into the Global Content Distribution System (GCDS) and the JKO Learning Management System (LMS) suite
of tools. This integration will enhance both synchronous (live) and asynchronous instructor-led training capabilities, providing
greater flexibility and accessibility for users. Efforts will focus on integrating Joint Training and Learning Architecture (JTLA)
across component tools such as LMS, Course Builder, Warrior Readiness Site (WRS), and VCLASS. This integration will support
advanced content development techniques, including micro-learning, parallax scrolling, and Adaptive Learning Methodology, to
deliver innovative and engaging training experiences.
The program will also extend the use of micro-learning technology, xAPI adaptation, Learning Record Store (LRS), and Adaptive
Learning Methodology to increase the personalization of learning content. Enhanced personalization capabilities will enable self-
regulated micro-learning training that is engaging, practical, and user-friendly. This approach allows individuals to quickly access
tailored learning content whenever opportunities arise, improving efficiency and effectiveness in training delivery.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Joint Knowledge Online (JKO) funds are to be realigned to JTEEP to support future integration and program enhancements
