dependence on obsolete desktop applications, which will lower future JASF development costs. Navy will identify solutions
to automate entity behavior(s) and maintain interoperability. Navy will focus on development of enhanced IAMD and BMD
capabilities to regularly improve requisite data models representing constructive ballistic missile threat systems and stimulation of
Navy, Joint, Service, Interagency, and Coalition live, virtual and constructive participants. Model sources include Missile Defense
Agency (MDA), National Air and Space Intelligence Center (NASIC) and Missile and Space Information Center (MSIC). JIP will
develop and incorporate constructive communications and systems to improve BLUFOR EW and ISR capabilities, while also
introducing BLUE counter OPFOR EW and ISR capabilities into realistic LVCt environments where the adversary degrades or
denies Joint Force ESM.
