FY 2025 Plans:
FY 2025 efforts will focus on initial acceptance testing, delivery, and fielding of production units to support User
Operational Evaluation System (UOES). Funding will provide additional investments in the transition of advanced
technologies as they are critical to the continued development and integration of key capabilities, including
improvements in cyber security, autonomy, and Automated Target Recognition efforts. These efforts will support
test and evaluation to demonstrate operational effectiveness and suitability.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
FY 2026 continues fielding baseline Lionfish production units. Funding will provide additional investments in
the transition of advanced technologies. Efforts will include continued development and evaluation of artificial
intelligence/machine learning algorithms, advanced autonomy behaviors and Automated Target Recognition
(ATR) development. In FY26, Lionfish will continue maturing the Foward Looking Sonar- 9 inch (FLS-9) for fleet
use and deliver increased capability through software updates to the vehicle's operating system and sensor
packages, including updates to the FLS ATR algorithms. Conduct Initial Operational Test and Evaluation due




