D. Acquisition Strategy
Advanced/Additive Manufacturing (AM) Strategy
The management approach includes the systems engineering oversight of capability and integration efforts.

1. Develop data and specifications for capability expansion
-Partner with industry through Cooperative Research and Development Activities (CRADAs) for standard and component development
-Partner with Military institutes
-Leverage public private institutes
-Leverage Naval Air Warfare Center (NAWC) laboratory personnel and facilities
-Contracted testing Tier 1 (desktop 3D polymer printer)
-Contracted material testing Tier 2 (industrial 3D polymer printers)
-Contracted automated Technical Data Package development leveraging Naval Air Warfare Center Aircraft Division (NAWCAD)
internal resources
-Leverage cross military working groups for candidate evaluation software

2. Develop requirements and evaluate systems for technical refresh
-Stakeholder input across Naval Aviation Enterprise (NAE)
-Analysis of Alternatives (AoA) conducted to determine state of the art
-Acquire and Evaluate candidate Tier 1 systems
-Evaluate candidate Tier 2 systems
-Acquire and Evaluate design software Tier 1 and Tier 2




