INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0604295M$$, 2026, $$Marine Aviation Demonstration/Validation supports the development of Marine Aviation's future capability concepts as part of Marine Corps Force Design and Marine
Corps Aviation's Project Eagle, progressing these concepts through development, demonstration and ultimately transition into fieldable capabilities This Program
Element (PE) funds development of United States Marine Corps (USMC) Vertical Take-Off and Landing (VTOL) capabilities, including manned and unmanned air
vehicles, and associated and requisite capabilities. Through development and prototyping, this PE matures and/or rapidly inserts industry and government technologies
into lethality gaps, enabling a cohesive, warfighter-centric approach towards a future lethality-based portfolio for Marine Aviation.

JUSTIFICATION FOR BUDGET ACTIVITY: This program is funded under ADVANCED COMPONENT DEVELOPMENT AND PROTOTYPES because it includes all
efforts necessary to evaluate integrated technologies, and representative models or prototype systems in a high fidelity and realistic operating environment.$$, $$The Future Capability Transition (FCT) portfolio implements a capabilities-based acquisition approach focused on lethality, enhancing Marine Corps Aviation's
interoperability and effectivity in joint kill webs. FCT accelerates the transition of Science and Technology (S&T) efforts into lethal Warfighter capabilities, which includes
OSD R&E Defense Innovation Acceleration (DIA) and OSD R&E Rapid Defense Experiment Reserve (RDER) projects. FCT supports the execution of Force Design by
ensuring both legacy and future platforms influence S&T early enough to inform design and acquisition decisions that avoid duplicative design and engineering, reduce
life-cycle costs and expedite delivery of enhanced lethality capabilities to Marine Aviation. This PE includes enduring VMX-1 RDT&E support along with support of Fleet
evaluations and demonstration.

