FY 2025 Plans:
Tasks to be performed include: Acquisition Program Management functions, Acquisition Documentation,
Engineering modeling and analysis, Test and Evaluation, planning and development. Cross-service collaboration
will continue via multiservice efforts enabling the Joint Capability Technology Demonstration (JCTD) Long Range
Attack Missile (LRAM), supported by the Army and Strategic Capabilities Office (SCO). Prior fiscal year work will
culminate in an FY 2025 capstone demonstration event and a Military Utility Assessment (MUA) where LRAM
will be demonstrated in an operationally relevant scenario prior to transition to PoR. Efforts will include working
with transition partners across the Services to ensure effective investment strategies resulting in capability
delivered to the Warfighter. Risk reduction efforts associated with MUX portfolio will include prototyping of
expeditionary air vehicle components and subsystems focused on launch and recovery, electronic warfare
subsystems and payloads, open architecture applications, and demonstration of these prototyping activities.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
LRAM JCTD, now LRAM Defense Innovator Accelerator (DIA), efforts complete in FY 2026. The ALE
project will further risk reduction, interoperability and prototyping efforts including kinetic/non-kinetic payload
development along with enhancements for in-flight targeting updates and terminal guidance. Future capability
assessments will occur to identify risk reduction opportunities for execution. These assessments may support

