FY 2025 Plans:
Tasks to be performed include: Acquisition Program Management functions, Acquisition Documentation,
Engineering modeling and analysis, Test and Evaluation planning and development, a Model Based System
Specification, continuation of the major operational demonstration contract with vendors participating in
Fleet exercises. Awarded operational demonstration vendors will perform tradespace analysis and design
review events to inform specification development and subsystem integration requirements for future platform
militarization efforts. Attack/Strike Concept Development and Technology Maturation (CDTM) efforts in critical
high-risk technology areas, culminating in design trade studies and rapid prototyping on associated systems,
include the Weapons Integration Risk Reduction (WIRR) OTA. Assault Support CDTM efforts will include trade
studies, virtual simulation, conceptual design, and prototyping of air vehicles. Additive manufacturing/propulsion



