 Area Denial (A2/AD) environments. The program will leverage and further advance foundational achievements in the joint Science and Technology (S&T) enterprise,
 making targeted investments in Navy integration of critical system attributes. User priorities, in the form of pacing the evolving maritime threat, will be the centerpiece of
 the system requirements and the associated development and fielding schedule. Additional details are classified.

 Project 3466 - The LRASM C-3 program is established to improve OASuW and incorporate a long range strike capability into the Navy's arsenal derived from the
 Navy's AGM-158C-1 LRASM and the Air Force's AGM-158 JASSM-ER. The Navy will integrate an AGM-158 derived weapon onto F/A-18 E/F aircraft. This funding
 line resources requirements for Navy increased LRASM capabilities and strike mission integration by upgrading the existing AGM-158C product to respond to rapidly
