FY 2025 Plans:
HM&E (WBS 1.0)- Integrate UMAA 6.0 compliant Engineering Operations (EO) aboard a sUSV platform to
achieve unmanned operations. This effort will establish the foundation for developing additional unmanned EO
capabilities planned for FY26.

Advanced Networks and Radios (WBS 2.0) - Increment 2 will be the core focus for unmanned communication
development. Capstone testing will continue for LOS and BLOS as well as unmanned cryptographic
development. C4I increment 2 prototypes will be integrated into USV representative networks for integration as
they are delivered.

USV Integrated Combat Systems (WBS 3.0) - USV ICS development work will continue in this project in the form
of integrating and transferring data obtained from a USV into USV ICS for use by a US Navy combatant. ICS test
events ahead of Capstone 4 will occur for data transfer supporting Capability Bundle development and LUSV
representative systems that will interface ICS, C4I, and CCS. ICS Capability Bundle #6 will begin navigation
integration and testing with ICS

Sensory Perception and Autonomy (WBS 5.0) - Demonstrated heterogenous operations of several USVs
equipped with UMAA 6.0 autonomy software at the Autonomous Warrior exercise.

Demonstrated the Minimum Viable Product (MVP) mission requirements for sUSVs, showcasing key capabilities
such as multi-boat formation maneuvers, squad loitering, obstacle avoidance, and third-party mission autonomy.

